>
  <style>
:root {
            --green: #10b981;
            --red: #ef4444;

}

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            color: var(--text-main);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        /* Sticky Nav */
        nav {
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            z-index: 1000;
            background-color: rgba(6, 10, 18, 0.85);
            backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding: 1rem 0;
        }

        .nav-content {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 0 1.5rem;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .brand {
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: var(--text-main);
            text-decoration: none;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
        }

        .nav-links {
            display: flex;
            gap: 1.5rem;
        }

        .nav-links a {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            transition: color 0.2s;
        }

        .nav-links a:hover {
            color: var(--accent-color);
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
        }

        header {
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
            text-align: center;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            background: linear-gradient(to right, #60a5fa, #3b82f6, #4a8fe7);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
            display: inline-block;
        }

        .subtitle {
            color: var(--text-muted);
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        /* ETF Selector */
        .selector-container {
            background-color: var(--card-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        .selector-title {
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .select-group {
            display: flex;
            gap: 1rem;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }

        select {
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            color: var(--text-main);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
            border-radius: 8px;
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            font-size: 1rem;
            flex: 1;
            min-width: 150px;
            outline: none;
        }

        select:focus {
            border-color: var(--accent-color);
        }

        /* Comparison Grid */
        .comparison-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 200px repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
            gap: 1px;
            background-color: var(--border-color);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 12px;
            overflow: hidden;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
        }

        .grid-cell {
            background-color: var(--card-bg);
            padding: 1rem;
        }

        .grid-header {
            font-weight: 700;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            text-align: center;
            background-color: rgba(74, 143, 231, 0.1);
            color: var(--accent-color);
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }

        .grid-label {
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--text-muted);
            background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
        }

        .grid-value {
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
            text-align: right;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: flex-end;
        }

        .value-green { color: var(--green); }
        .value-red { color: var(--red); }

        .section-header {
            grid-column: 1 / -1;
            background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.05em;
            color: var(--text-muted);
        }

        /* Charts */
        .charts-container {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
        }

        .chart-card {
            background-color: var(--card-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 1.5rem;
        }

        .chart-title {
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            text-align: center;
        }

        /* Holdings List */
        .holdings-list {
            list-style: none;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }
        .holdings-list li {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
        }
        .holdings-list li:last-child {
            border-bottom: none;
            margin-bottom: 0;
            padding-bottom: 0;
        }
        .h-symbol { font-weight: 600; }
        .h-percent { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; color: var(--text-muted); }

        /* Content Sections */
        .content-section {
            background-color: var(--card-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            color: var(--text-main);
        }

        .faq-item {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        .faq-item h3 {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            color: var(--accent-color);
        }

        .faq-item p {
            color: var(--text-muted);
        }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            color: var(--text-muted);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            margin-top: 2rem;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .charts-container {
                grid-template-columns: 1fr;
            }
            .comparison-grid {
                overflow-x: auto;
            }
            .nav-links {
                display: none;
            }
        }
  </style>

<div class="container">
    <h1>ETF Comparison Tool: Side-by-Side Analysis</h1>


        <div class="selector-container">
            <div class="selector-title">Select ETFs to Compare</div>
            <div class="select-group">
                <select id="etf1" onchange="updateComparison()"></select>
                <select id="etf2" onchange="updateComparison()"></select>
                <select id="etf3" onchange="updateComparison()">
                    <option value="">-- None --</option>
                </select>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div id="comparison-container">
            <!-- Grid will be injected here -->
        </div>

        <div class="charts-container">
            <div class="chart-card">
                <div class="chart-title">Historical Returns</div>
                <canvas id="returnsChart"></canvas>
            </div>
            <div class="chart-card">
                <div class="chart-title">Sector Allocation</div>
                <canvas id="sectorsChart"></canvas>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section">
            <h2>Methodology & Data Sources</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                This tool provides a side-by-side comparison of exchange-traded funds (ETFs). The data presented is updated periodically and is sourced from Yahoo Finance API.
            </p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-muted); margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                <li><strong>Expense Ratio:</strong> The annual fee charged by the fund, expressed as a percentage of assets.</li>
                <li><strong>AUM (Assets Under Management):</strong> Total market value of assets the fund manages.</li>
                <li><strong>Yield:</strong> Trailing 12-month dividend yield.</li>
                <li><strong>Returns:</strong> Trailing total returns (including dividends) as of the most recent month-end.</li>
                <li><strong>Holdings:</strong> The top 10 individual stock components of the ETF.</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">
                Note: All metrics are approximations and should be verified via the fund sponsor's official prospectus before making investment decisions.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-section">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>How does VOO compare to VTI?</h3>
                <p>VOO tracks the S&P 500, holding roughly 500 of the largest U.S. companies. VTI tracks the entire U.S. stock market, holding over 3,000 large, mid, and small-cap stocks. Both have extremely low expense ratios, and historically, their returns have been highly correlated because VTI's performance is heavily weighted by the same large-cap companies that make up VOO.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>What is the difference between SPY, VOO, and IVV?</h3>
                <p>SPY, VOO, and IVV all track the S&P 500 index. Their primary differences are their ETF sponsors (State Street, Vanguard, and BlackRock, respectively) and their expense ratios. VOO and IVV typically have slightly lower expense ratios than SPY, while SPY generally has higher daily trading volume, making it popular for options trading.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>How to compare ETF overlap?</h3>
                <p>You can compare ETF overlap by examining the underlying top holdings and sector weightings. Our tool allows you to select multiple ETFs and directly compare their top 10 holdings and sector allocations side-by-side to identify potential concentration risks.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Which ETF has the highest dividend yield?</h3>
                <p>Among popular ETFs, those focused on dividend strategies (like SCHD or VYM) or covered call strategies (like JEPI or JEPQ) typically offer higher dividend yields compared to broad market ETFs like VOO or VTI. Yields fluctuate based on market prices and recent distributions.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Is it better to have QQQ or VOO?</h3>
                <p>It depends on your investment goals and risk tolerance. QQQ tracks the tech-heavy Nasdaq-100 index, which has historically provided higher growth but comes with greater volatility and concentration in the technology sector. VOO provides broader diversification across 500 large-cap companies in various sectors.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
